# Next.js App Router

## Routes (from PRD)

- `/` — today view (default landing)
- `/day/[date]` — `YYYY-MM-DD` day view
- `/weight` — weight log + chart
- `/settings` — daily calorie target
- `app/api/estimate/route.ts` — POST only; Anthropic proxy

## Patterns

- Use Server Components for static shell; `"use client"` for Firestore listeners, bottom sheets, swipe nav, forms.
- Colocate route-specific components under `components/` by domain (`meals/`, `weight/`, `layout/`).
- API routes return typed JSON errors; never leak stack traces or API keys in responses.
- Use `loading.tsx` / `error.tsx` per route where UX benefits; meal rows use inline optimistic state instead of full-page loading for estimates.

## Avoid

- Server Actions for Firestore writes (client SDK + rules is the chosen pattern).
- Putting Firebase Admin or Anthropic SDK in client bundles.
